# Adding Blogs & Changelogs

When adding blog posts or changelog entries, follow these patterns.

## Changelog (What's New)

- Stored in Supabase `app_config` key `changelog`
- Add via SQL migration in `frontend/db/migrations/`
- Use `jsonb_build_array(new_entry) || (current_changelog->'entries')` to prepend
- Fields: `version`, `date`, `title`, `type`, `description`, `features`, `fixes`
- See `085_changelog_and_blog_march_2025.sql` for full template

## Blog

Three places to update:

1. **`frontend/lib/blog-defaults.ts`** — Add entry to `DEFAULT_BLOG_POSTS` (metadata: slug, title, excerpt, date, author, category, readTime, gradient, icon, imageUrl?).
2. **`frontend/app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`** — Add to `blogContent` object with full markdown `content`.
3. **SQL migration** (optional) — Add to `app_config.blog` via same pattern as changelog.

Categories: `Announcement`, `Budget Building`, `Strategy`, `Commander`.

## Full Guide

See `frontend/docs/HOW_TO_ADD_BLOGS_AND_CHANGELOGS.md` for step-by-step instructions and SQL templates.
